The paper deals with erasure list-decoding algorithms for expander codes, which are typically studied in the context of information theory (cs.IT) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS, cs.CC). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
